severe cramps that come and go during rd trimester of pregnancy i am weeks pregnant and i have been having sever cramps in my lower back and in my stomach by my belly button that go all the way around and down to my lower abdominal area the cramps in my stomach will hit mainly at night or when i am on my feet and stay for a while then they will ease up for a bit and come back but the cramps in my lower back stay for a while my doctor put me on some muscle relaxers without checking me to see if i was dilated or leaking fluid is this normal or could it be early labor sounds like contractions if you are getting more than in an hour call your doctor and call them anyway to let them know your symptoms early contractions can sometimes be due to dehydration so make sure you are drinking water at least glasses per day good luck and talk to your doctor about this don't just ignore it early contractions can be no big deal but if you wait to long you can end up with pre term labor Obstetrics Miscarriage Urinary incontinence Abortion Stomach cancer Dehydration Gastroparesis Cramp Equine conformation Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Diabetic retinopathy Premature birth Breech birth Aortic dissection Dialysis Diarrhea Intact dilation and extraction Breastfeeding Cholera Cirrhosis Poker jargon Decompression sickness Fecal incontinence Menstrual cycle Endometriosis Abdominal pain Prostate cancer Abdomen Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Hyperthermia Adjustable gastric band Morning sickness Endometrial cancer Cephalic disorder Osteoarthritis Dieting Shock Social rule Coffee Anxiety Pneumonia Insomnia Haloperidol 3-quinuclidinyl benzilate Hypoglycemia Vomiting Big Brother UK series 6 Diabetes mellitus Abortion debate Sulfasalazine Acute pancreatitis Professional wrestling holds Stuttering Hatha yoga Aerial (dance move) Traumatic brain injury Partial-birth abortion Hemorrhoid Drowning Dysentery Oasis (band) Ectopic pregnancy Weight training Bruise Caffeine Glycogen storage disease type I Hear